1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:02,800
<i>Leon said that he was
investigating someone.</i>

2
00:00:02,933 --> 00:00:05,133
<i> He killed him with his car.</i>

3
00:00:05,500 --> 00:00:07,033
<i> I didn't want to kill anyone.</i>

4
00:00:07,133 --> 00:00:08,633
<i> But that guy is a monster.</i>

5
00:00:08,933 --> 00:00:11,633
<i>If I hadn't killed him,
they would kill Dad instead.</i>

6
00:00:11,967 --> 00:00:14,600
<i>What does Uncle Andy
have to do with any of that?</i>

7
00:00:14,767 --> 00:00:18,100
<i>Because Andy and Sandro,
who wanted to kill Dad,</i>

8
00:00:18,467 --> 00:00:20,067
<i> conspired together.</i>

9
00:00:20,333 --> 00:00:24,300
<i>They believe that there's
hidden treasure in Hotel 88.</i>

10
00:00:25,267 --> 00:00:26,733
<i> Hey! Hey! Hey!</i>

11
00:00:26,833 --> 00:00:28,467
<i> Let me go! Hey!</i>

12
00:00:28,633 --> 00:00:31,133
<i>They've been looking for you
for a long time now.</i>

13
00:00:31,300 --> 00:00:32,400
<i> Almazan.</i>

14
00:00:32,533 --> 00:00:35,067
<i>We received a report that
Juan Soliman was kidnapped.</i>

15
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:36,900
Wait a second. I don't know him.

16
00:00:37,033 --> 00:00:38,300
<i> Check the back.</i>

17
00:00:39,467 --> 00:00:41,267
<i>We're arresting you
for the kidnapping</i>

18
00:00:41,367 --> 00:00:43,567
<i> and murder of Juan Soliman!</i>

19
00:00:46,267 --> 00:00:47,667
Luna, what happened
to our brother?

20
00:00:47,800 --> 00:00:48,667
Why was he arrested?

21
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:50,300
He's being accused of murder.

22
00:00:50,433 --> 00:00:51,833
Justin, have you called
our lawyer yet?

23
00:00:51,967 --> 00:00:53,100
Yes, she's on her way now.

24
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:55,167
What about Mom?
We need to call her!

25
00:00:55,300 --> 00:00:57,900
- I have to--
- For what? To make her worried?

26
00:00:58,033 --> 00:01:00,333
Mom needs to know
what's happening to Leon!

27
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:02,167
We don't even know
the whole story, Jade!

28
00:01:02,300 --> 00:01:03,667
We'll just give her
a panic attack.

29
00:01:03,833 --> 00:01:05,933
[JUSTIN] Luna, Jade, we need
to get going! Just argue later.

30
00:01:06,033 --> 00:01:07,100
But, Luna--

31
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:09,400
We will call Mom once
we know everything.

32
00:01:09,533 --> 00:01:12,000
Instead of making her worry,
let's focus on Leon first, okay?

33
00:01:12,167 --> 00:01:14,000
Just hurry up!

34
00:01:14,167 --> 00:01:15,200
[JUSTIN SCOFFS]

35
00:01:15,367 --> 00:01:22,367
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

36
00:01:37,333 --> 00:01:44,333
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

37
00:01:59,367 --> 00:02:06,367
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

38
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:21,833
[WAVES CRASHING]

39
00:02:21,933 --> 00:02:28,767
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

40
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:35,667
Dad.

41
00:02:37,267 --> 00:02:39,700
It's been a long time since
we've done this together.

42
00:02:40,567 --> 00:02:43,233
[ANDY] Well, you know
it's not for a lack of want.

43
00:02:43,367 --> 00:02:45,767
I'm no longer the only one
you spend your time with.

44
00:02:45,933 --> 00:02:49,233
I wouldn't be surprised if
you'd invite Jade here too.

45
00:02:49,433 --> 00:02:50,933
[FISHING REEL SCREAMING]

46
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:53,133
[EDWARD] We're just
both busy, Dad.

47
00:02:53,300 --> 00:02:55,800
I'm not even sure if
I still know how to do this.

48
00:02:55,967 --> 00:02:58,800
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

49
00:02:58,967 --> 00:03:01,033
What are you talking about?

50
00:03:01,133 --> 00:03:02,400
Look, you're just
out of practice.

51
00:03:02,500 --> 00:03:04,133
You're not out of skill.

52
00:03:04,933 --> 00:03:11,767
[FISHING REEL DRAGGING]

53
00:03:13,967 --> 00:03:18,967
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

54
00:03:19,133 --> 00:03:21,267
Why so impatient, buddy?

55
00:03:22,867 --> 00:03:24,567
It's just been a while.

56
00:03:26,500 --> 00:03:28,400
Don't I always tell you that

57
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:31,000
patience is an underrated skill.

58
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:34,833
If you want to catch
whatever you want to catch,

59
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:38,067
you need to know when to wait,

60
00:03:38,167 --> 00:03:40,333
when to pull,

61
00:03:40,500 --> 00:03:42,800
and when you won't do anything.

62
00:03:42,967 --> 00:03:44,667
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

63
00:03:44,833 --> 00:03:47,000
Even when I'm supposed
to not do anything?

64
00:03:47,167 --> 00:03:49,000
Especially if you have
to do nothing

65
00:03:49,167 --> 00:03:51,233
because it's all about
the timing.

66
00:03:51,333 --> 00:03:58,167
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

67
00:03:58,367 --> 00:03:59,533
[LUNA PANTING]

68
00:03:59,700 --> 00:04:01,167
Leon Almazan.

69
00:04:01,333 --> 00:04:02,833
Let's go!

70
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:06,333
Leon? Leon!

71
00:04:06,500 --> 00:04:08,533
- Leon!
- Leon.

72
00:04:08,700 --> 00:04:11,133
Oh my god, Leon. Oh my god!

73
00:04:11,233 --> 00:04:13,333
What did they do to you?

74
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:15,667
Brother! [CRYING]

75
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:18,833
[JADE SOBBING]
What happened to you?

76
00:04:18,967 --> 00:04:20,667
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

77
00:04:20,833 --> 00:04:26,367
[JADE SOBBING] Oh my god,
what happened to you?

78
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:29,100
What happened, Leon?

79
00:04:29,233 --> 00:04:30,300
[SNIFFLES]

80
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:32,200
I also don't know.

81
00:04:32,367 --> 00:04:34,700
[INHALES SHARPLY]
But I'm being framed.

82
00:04:36,333 --> 00:04:39,700
[LEON] Don't make
any statements yet.

83
00:04:39,867 --> 00:04:42,167
Let's leave this up to
our lawyer for now.

84
00:04:42,267 --> 00:04:44,200
- Leon...
- Who is it?

85
00:04:44,900 --> 00:04:46,867
Who was the person
you allegedly killed?

86
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,800
I can't tell you here, Justin.

87
00:04:48,900 --> 00:04:50,667
Not here.

88
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:53,367
[SNIFFLES] Leon...

89
00:04:53,533 --> 00:04:55,400
Are they letting you eat here?

90
00:04:55,567 --> 00:04:56,700
Everything is going to be okay.

91
00:04:56,867 --> 00:04:59,533
But what about you?
How will you fare here?

92
00:04:59,667 --> 00:05:02,167
- How can you eat here?
- [LEON] Stay strong.

93
00:05:02,300 --> 00:05:03,900
- We'll visit you again.
- No, please!

94
00:05:04,067 --> 00:05:06,433
- I'll only be here briefly.
- We need you, Leon!

95
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:09,033
[JADE] Release my brother
right now!

96
00:05:09,133 --> 00:05:10,900
[JADE] All of you, please!

97
00:05:11,067 --> 00:05:13,733
- Please release him!
- Our brother's not a murderer.

98
00:05:13,867 --> 00:05:14,667
Let him go!

99
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:17,567
Ms. Almazan,
I personally saw the corpse

100
00:05:17,733 --> 00:05:20,000
in the back of
your brother's car.

101
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:21,333
[JADE] What?!

102
00:05:21,433 --> 00:05:23,900
Leon could never do that.

103
00:05:25,633 --> 00:05:28,400
The evidence against Leon
is incriminating.

104
00:05:28,567 --> 00:05:30,333
The victim personally reported
that Leon abducted him

105
00:05:30,433 --> 00:05:32,233
before he was found dead.

106
00:05:32,367 --> 00:05:34,167
My brother has no enemies,
so whoever that is--

107
00:05:34,300 --> 00:05:35,267
[HENRI] It's Soliman.

108
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:37,700
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

109
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:40,100
[MARINA] We found
Juan Soliman's body

110
00:05:40,233 --> 00:05:41,933
in your brother's car.

111
00:05:43,333 --> 00:05:45,433
Do you know the victim?

112
00:05:47,400 --> 00:05:49,800
We don't know who that is.

113
00:05:49,967 --> 00:05:51,433
Set my brother free.

114
00:05:52,567 --> 00:05:55,067
The lawyers are already
taking care of your case.

115
00:05:55,967 --> 00:05:57,633
So, just wait here.

116
00:05:58,333 --> 00:06:02,267
[JADE BREATHING HEAVILY]

117
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:09,900
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

118
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:15,800
- Our brother...
- It's okay. It's okay.

119
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:19,433
[EDWARD] Dad, there's
still no movement.

120
00:06:20,333 --> 00:06:21,800
Wait.

121
00:06:21,933 --> 00:06:24,233
Wait for it.

122
00:06:24,333 --> 00:06:25,167
[WATER SPLASHES]

123
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:27,067
There we go!

124
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:28,133
There it is.

125
00:06:28,467 --> 00:06:31,133
- [FISHING REEL SCREAMING]
- [GRUNTING] There we go.

126
00:06:31,267 --> 00:06:34,833
What did I tell you? [LAUGHING]

127
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,467
Ahh.

128
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:40,800
What did I say?

129
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,300
There you go.

130
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:44,467
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

131
00:06:44,567 --> 00:06:49,167
Don't people say that
a fish is caught by its mouth?

132
00:06:49,333 --> 00:06:52,667
For me, they get caught...

133
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:56,167
when they don't even know
they're being fished.

134
00:06:56,300 --> 00:07:01,000
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

135
00:07:01,133 --> 00:07:02,833
All about timing.

136
00:07:02,967 --> 00:07:04,433
[CHUCKLING]

137
00:07:12,367 --> 00:07:13,967
What even is this?

138
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:15,633
Monocular?

139
00:07:16,533 --> 00:07:19,067
Is it to magnify where
the treasure is?

140
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:21,033
It seems like it.

141
00:07:22,033 --> 00:07:23,867
And that's a compass?

142
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,700
[CLEARS THROAT] Yes.

143
00:07:26,733 --> 00:07:28,533
It looks pretty but
it's just a compass.

144
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:31,233
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

145
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:33,367
I don't even know
if we can really use this

146
00:07:33,533 --> 00:07:35,233
to find that treasure.

147
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:36,533
Because, what if...

148
00:07:37,433 --> 00:07:39,067
it's just one of
Papa's mementos?

149
00:07:40,767 --> 00:07:44,400
I don't think he'll hide that
if it's part of his collection.

150
00:07:44,567 --> 00:07:46,233
Just like that, for example.

151
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:47,667
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

152
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:51,033
If it's part of his collection,
he'd display it like those.

153
00:07:52,233 --> 00:07:53,700
[MARTIN] Makes sense.

154
00:07:54,900 --> 00:07:58,700
And this book might also
have a hidden meaning.

155
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:01,400
[KIKO] A double meaning.

156
00:08:01,533 --> 00:08:03,500
I've seen things like that
in movies.

157
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:05,500
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

158
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:07,700
[GIO EXHALES DEEPLY]

159
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:10,567
What now, Martin?

160
00:08:10,733 --> 00:08:12,100
Is Leon still not here?

161
00:08:12,267 --> 00:08:13,200
Not yet.

162
00:08:13,300 --> 00:08:15,733
He's not answering my calls too.

163
00:08:16,067 --> 00:08:18,367
Maybe he's still driving
on his way here.

164
00:08:18,567 --> 00:08:19,900
You told him a while ago, right?

165
00:08:20,033 --> 00:08:21,067
Mm-hmm.

166
00:08:21,267 --> 00:08:23,067
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

167
00:08:23,167 --> 00:08:24,700
[CELLPHONE RINGING]

168
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:26,067
It's getting late already.

169
00:08:26,167 --> 00:08:30,200
[RINGING CONTINUES]

170
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:33,367
Luna.

171
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:35,567
[LUNA]<i> Gio, we're here at
</i> the police station right now.

172
00:08:35,667 --> 00:08:37,800
<i>They arrested Leon.
They said he killed someone.</i>

173
00:08:37,967 --> 00:08:39,067
Leon?

174
00:08:39,167 --> 00:08:40,633
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

175
00:08:40,800 --> 00:08:42,533
He killed someone?

176
00:08:42,633 --> 00:08:44,267
[LUNA]<i> We don't know
</i> the details yet.

177
00:08:44,433 --> 00:08:45,433
<i> I'll just keep you updated.</i>

178
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:47,267
No, we're going there, Luna.

179
00:08:51,733 --> 00:08:53,867
Let's just wait for
the lawyer to call us.

180
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:05,000
Luna, where's Leon?

181
00:09:05,167 --> 00:09:06,267
[LUNA] He's inside.

182
00:09:07,433 --> 00:09:09,100
What did really happen?

183
00:09:10,533 --> 00:09:12,300
Let's talk outside.

184
00:09:12,433 --> 00:09:19,267
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

185
00:09:25,167 --> 00:09:28,833
Someone reported to the police
that Juan Soliman got abducted.

186
00:09:31,167 --> 00:09:32,200
Juan?

187
00:09:32,867 --> 00:09:34,867
- The--
- [LUNA] Yes, Gio.

188
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:37,167
Juan Soliman.

189
00:09:39,900 --> 00:09:42,000
We don't know anyone
named Juan Soliman.

190
00:09:43,167 --> 00:09:44,767
Whoever that may be,

191
00:09:44,867 --> 00:09:46,533
I'm sure that
my brother didn't kill him.

192
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:50,833
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

193
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:56,800
Why can't the attorney
release Leon?

194
00:09:56,967 --> 00:09:58,267
Luna, this can't be!

195
00:09:58,367 --> 00:10:00,633
It's more complicated
than it looks, Jade.

196
00:10:01,700 --> 00:10:03,300
The case against Leon
isn't that easy.

197
00:10:03,933 --> 00:10:05,667
I'm going to call Mom.

198
00:10:05,767 --> 00:10:07,533
- We can't hide this from her.
- Jade.

199
00:10:07,700 --> 00:10:08,867
I'll go with her.

200
00:10:10,867 --> 00:10:17,700
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

201
00:10:17,833 --> 00:10:19,833
Leon's already
in the visiting area.

202
00:10:19,933 --> 00:10:22,667
I'll talk to him,
ask him how he is.

203
00:10:22,767 --> 00:10:24,367
And, Luna...

204
00:10:24,533 --> 00:10:25,867
Don't worry about work first.

205
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,400
We'll take care of the hotel.

206
00:10:27,567 --> 00:10:34,367
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

207
00:10:40,433 --> 00:10:41,700
But Juan...

208
00:10:43,767 --> 00:10:46,000
Justin, you better confess
right now.

209
00:10:46,767 --> 00:10:48,400
- Do you have anything to do--
- Me?

210
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:51,033
Kill Juan? No!

211
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:54,933
You know him.

212
00:10:55,067 --> 00:10:56,933
And you know
about the treasure.

213
00:10:58,433 --> 00:10:59,600
I know.

214
00:10:59,733 --> 00:11:01,100
But I didn't kill him.

215
00:11:04,533 --> 00:11:05,700
Okay.

216
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:08,100
I just needed
to hear that from you.

217
00:11:12,467 --> 00:11:13,900
Justin, listen.

218
00:11:15,067 --> 00:11:17,733
I can't do anything
while I'm here.

219
00:11:18,733 --> 00:11:22,100
So don't do anything
that will ruin our family.

220
00:11:22,267 --> 00:11:24,600
I'm not stupid enough
to add to our problems.

221
00:11:24,767 --> 00:11:26,100
I'm just saying...

222
00:11:26,967 --> 00:11:29,033
Whoever did this to me...

223
00:11:29,767 --> 00:11:31,800
They want to destroy
our family.

224
00:11:32,767 --> 00:11:35,233
You all need to be careful.

225
00:11:38,433 --> 00:11:39,767
We're going to fight, Leon.

226
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:43,967
I'll do everything
to prove you're innocent.

227
00:11:47,100 --> 00:11:49,233
[JADE] Mom, Leon needs you here.

228
00:11:49,967 --> 00:11:52,433
We need you here, Mom.
Please come home.

229
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:53,667
[FRIDA] I will.

230
00:11:54,700 --> 00:11:55,933
<i> Jade, my dear...</i>

231
00:11:56,800 --> 00:11:58,900
<i> I know this is hard for you.</i>

232
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:01,133
<i>But I need you
to be strong for Leon.</i>

233
00:12:01,300 --> 00:12:02,800
Yes, Mom.

234
00:12:02,967 --> 00:12:03,833
Yes.

235
00:12:04,767 --> 00:12:06,000
<i> I will come home.</i>

236
00:12:06,800 --> 00:12:08,000
<i> I love you, Jade.</i>

237
00:12:09,467 --> 00:12:10,767
I love you too, Mom.

238
00:12:15,167 --> 00:12:16,133
[PHONE BEEPS]

239
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:20,300
Mom's coming home.

240
00:12:22,367 --> 00:12:23,333
Jade.

241
00:12:25,167 --> 00:12:27,800
I'm sure Aunt Frida
is also worried.

242
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:36,833
[PHONE RINGING]

243
00:12:44,667 --> 00:12:45,600
[KIKO CLEARS THROAT]

244
00:12:45,700 --> 00:12:47,667
[PHONE CONTINUES RINGING]

245
00:12:49,367 --> 00:12:50,233
Hello?

246
00:12:50,867 --> 00:12:52,300
Jade, where are you?

247
00:12:53,367 --> 00:12:55,500
Monette told me
about what happened to Leon.

248
00:12:56,367 --> 00:12:57,867
[JADE] We're still
at the police station.

249
00:13:00,033 --> 00:13:02,200
I'll go there. I'm on my way.

250
00:13:02,367 --> 00:13:04,333
[JADE]<i> Edward, don't bother.
</i> We're about to leave, anyway.

251
00:13:06,867 --> 00:13:08,900
Jade, I want to be there
for you.

252
00:13:09,533 --> 00:13:10,967
I know.

253
00:13:11,767 --> 00:13:14,000
And I appreciate you for that,
but Edward...

254
00:13:14,933 --> 00:13:17,367
Can you leave me be for now?
Everything's still a mess.

255
00:13:21,700 --> 00:13:22,733
No, Jade.

256
00:13:22,900 --> 00:13:25,667
I want to be there for you
right this moment.

257
00:13:25,767 --> 00:13:27,367
Right when
everything's uncertain.

258
00:13:27,533 --> 00:13:28,533
Edward!

259
00:13:29,733 --> 00:13:30,733
[EDWARD] Jade, I don't--

260
00:13:30,900 --> 00:13:32,533
<i> I don't understand.</i>

261
00:13:32,700 --> 00:13:33,833
Bye, Edward.

262
00:13:33,933 --> 00:13:34,833
[PHONE BEEPS]

263
00:13:34,933 --> 00:13:36,367
[LINE DROPS]

264
00:13:37,467 --> 00:13:44,367
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

265
00:13:46,467 --> 00:13:47,367
Jade.

266
00:13:49,033 --> 00:13:50,233
If you want to cry...

267
00:13:51,867 --> 00:13:52,900
It's okay.

268
00:13:53,567 --> 00:13:54,500
You can cry.

269
00:13:55,900 --> 00:13:58,900
Everyone says I have
to be strong.

270
00:14:00,100 --> 00:14:02,467
But does crying mean
you're weak?

271
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:09,033
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

272
00:14:09,133 --> 00:14:11,033
My siblings might see me.

273
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:14,567
We'll keep it a secret.

274
00:14:16,100 --> 00:14:19,133
With me,
you can stop acting strong.

275
00:14:20,133 --> 00:14:21,967
Don't worry.
I'll take care of you.

276
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:27,033
We'll be like this.

277
00:14:28,100 --> 00:14:29,767
I'm going to hide you
behind my back,

278
00:14:29,967 --> 00:14:32,067
so that no one sees you.

279
00:14:33,133 --> 00:14:36,333
And so you can cry
as much as you want.

280
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:39,333
[JADE SNIFFLES]

281
00:14:43,133 --> 00:14:44,500
We're best friends, Jade.

282
00:14:47,800 --> 00:14:51,100
You can use my back
for now, while...

283
00:14:55,800 --> 00:14:56,767
...Edward isn't here.

284
00:14:56,933 --> 00:15:03,267
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

285
00:15:03,400 --> 00:15:04,800
[INHALES SHARPLY]

286
00:15:04,900 --> 00:15:06,467
[EXHALES SHAKILY]

287
00:15:09,667 --> 00:15:12,433
[JADE BREATHES SHAKILY]

288
00:15:15,900 --> 00:15:22,133
[CRYING]

289
00:15:24,833 --> 00:15:26,167
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

290
00:15:26,333 --> 00:15:28,267
[JADE CRYING]

291
00:15:31,067 --> 00:15:37,500
[JADE CRYING]

292
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:42,400
[MARTIN] Someone set you up?

293
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:46,233
And I already suspect who.

294
00:15:46,367 --> 00:15:49,233
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

295
00:15:49,367 --> 00:15:50,800
[WHISPERS] Andy?

296
00:15:53,167 --> 00:15:54,167
[MARTIN SIGHS]

297
00:15:54,833 --> 00:15:56,367
Because of the hotel?

298
00:15:56,533 --> 00:15:58,367
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

299
00:15:58,533 --> 00:16:01,333
That's the only issue my family
is dealing with right now.

300
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:02,800
[EXHALES HEAVILY]

301
00:16:02,900 --> 00:16:06,033
Well, do you think
we should tell the cops?

302
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:07,833
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

303
00:16:07,933 --> 00:16:09,967
I have no evidence yet, bro.

304
00:16:10,100 --> 00:16:13,500
But I'm pretty sure it was
Uncle Andy who did this to me.

305
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:14,867
Shh.

306
00:16:17,867 --> 00:16:19,167
Bro.

307
00:16:19,300 --> 00:16:23,367
From now on, you need
to watch your words.

308
00:16:23,533 --> 00:16:26,233
You're up against
a really powerful guy.

309
00:16:26,367 --> 00:16:27,333
Okay?

310
00:16:27,433 --> 00:16:29,900
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

311
00:16:30,033 --> 00:16:31,167
[EXHALES HEAVILY]

312
00:16:34,233 --> 00:16:35,367
Gio, about my brother...

313
00:16:35,467 --> 00:16:37,233
What if...

314
00:16:37,367 --> 00:16:38,767
What if it's true?

315
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:48,233
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

316
00:16:54,567 --> 00:16:56,033
[LUNA] Thank you.

317
00:16:56,167 --> 00:16:57,900
I just can't wrap my head
around the fact

318
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:00,567
that his corpse was found
in my brother's car.

319
00:17:01,400 --> 00:17:03,733
We'll prove that he had
nothing to do with it.

320
00:17:04,500 --> 00:17:05,433
That...

321
00:17:05,567 --> 00:17:06,933
he was set up by someone.

322
00:17:07,067 --> 00:17:09,233
Sure, but how did it get there?

323
00:17:09,333 --> 00:17:10,300
Luna.

324
00:17:10,433 --> 00:17:11,533
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

325
00:17:11,667 --> 00:17:13,367
One thing at a time.

326
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:16,800
What matters right now is that
you know what you believe in.

327
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:21,300
Honestly, Gio, I don't know
what to believe anymore.

328
00:17:23,033 --> 00:17:25,000
Are you doubting
your brother?

329
00:17:25,167 --> 00:17:26,300
Of course not.

330
00:17:26,433 --> 00:17:28,133
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

331
00:17:28,267 --> 00:17:29,800
I have no doubts.

332
00:17:30,933 --> 00:17:33,000
I'm just really scared, Gio.

333
00:17:34,533 --> 00:17:35,967
Fear is normal.

334
00:17:38,333 --> 00:17:39,967
Just don't give up.

335
00:17:41,167 --> 00:17:42,133
[JUSTIN] Luna!

336
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:46,733
We need to talk.

337
00:17:47,533 --> 00:17:48,833
Okay, I'll call Jade.

338
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:50,033
No.

339
00:17:50,167 --> 00:17:51,333
Let's meet at home.

340
00:17:52,733 --> 00:17:54,100
Bring your brothers, too.

341
00:18:03,967 --> 00:18:05,933
Justin, what do you have
to say to us?

342
00:18:11,300 --> 00:18:14,133
There's only one reason
why all of this is happening.

343
00:18:15,700 --> 00:18:17,300
I'm talking
about Andy Arellano.

344
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:19,367
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

345
00:18:19,533 --> 00:18:21,367
No one else has the motive
but him.

346
00:18:23,267 --> 00:18:26,000
[JADE] And how can you
be sure of that, Justin?

347
00:18:31,733 --> 00:18:34,233
I was the last one with him
before he died.

348
00:18:34,367 --> 00:18:35,300
What?

349
00:18:35,433 --> 00:18:38,133
[MARTIN] So, you talked
to Juan before he passed?

350
00:18:38,233 --> 00:18:39,333
Yes.

351
00:18:39,433 --> 00:18:41,000
And he himself told me

352
00:18:41,100 --> 00:18:44,000
that it was Uncle Andy's men
who had kidnapped him.

353
00:18:44,100 --> 00:18:45,233
[JUAN] Sir Andy.

354
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:46,700
<i> That's what they called him.</i>

355
00:18:46,867 --> 00:18:48,700
[JUSTIN]
<i> So, he's the mastermind?</i>

356
00:18:48,833 --> 00:18:51,033
[JUAN]<i> They're hunting
</i> my father through me.

357
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:52,633
<i> Just like us,</i>

358
00:18:52,733 --> 00:18:54,500
<i>they're desperate
for the treasure.</i>

359
00:18:54,600 --> 00:19:01,700
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

360
00:19:04,200 --> 00:19:05,167
What?

361
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:08,567
I'm not making this up, Jade.

362
00:19:09,433 --> 00:19:12,500
He got away, and I was
the first person he went to.

363
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:14,600
I told him to leave the island,

364
00:19:14,767 --> 00:19:17,100
knowing Uncle Andy isn't
someone you mess with.

365
00:19:17,267 --> 00:19:18,233
But in the end...

366
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:20,267
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

367
00:19:20,433 --> 00:19:22,033
he died.

368
00:19:22,133 --> 00:19:24,933
So you're saying that Andy
had Juan kidnapped,

369
00:19:25,100 --> 00:19:27,533
then killed,
and put in Leon's car?

370
00:19:27,633 --> 00:19:28,833
Who else would have done that?

371
00:19:28,967 --> 00:19:30,733
That's what Leon thinks, too.

372
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:33,633
Is it because
of the partnership?

373
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:36,267
Leon didn't want him
to be a partner.

374
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:39,633
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

375
00:19:39,800 --> 00:19:40,967
[JUSTIN HUFFS]

376
00:19:42,800 --> 00:19:44,767
I need to come clean.

377
00:19:47,900 --> 00:19:50,267
The police should know
everything I know.

378
00:19:54,767 --> 00:19:56,733
So, are we going
to tell the police

379
00:19:56,833 --> 00:19:59,067
that it was Andy
who killed Juan?

380
00:19:59,167 --> 00:20:00,133
- Yes!
- No!

381
00:20:00,300 --> 00:20:01,700
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

382
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:03,433
What proof do we have
against Andy?

383
00:20:03,633 --> 00:20:04,967
Juan's own words!

384
00:20:05,133 --> 00:20:06,667
[GIO] Do you expect
the police to believe

385
00:20:06,833 --> 00:20:08,467
that a dead man told you that?

386
00:20:08,633 --> 00:20:11,067
What if that's the only thing
that could help Leon go free?

387
00:20:11,167 --> 00:20:13,967
Unless you have evidence,
that's not going to happen.

388
00:20:14,133 --> 00:20:15,467
You'll just get yourself
into trouble.

389
00:20:15,633 --> 00:20:17,500
[KIKO] And Jade and Luna, too.

390
00:20:17,667 --> 00:20:24,267
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

391
00:20:24,367 --> 00:20:25,800
What if there's evidence?

392
00:20:25,967 --> 00:20:28,133
[LUNA] Justin, let's consult
with the attorneys.

393
00:20:28,300 --> 00:20:29,833
They'll take care of it.

394
00:20:31,367 --> 00:20:32,933
Maybe Cheska has a video.

395
00:20:35,167 --> 00:20:36,267
Cheska?

396
00:20:37,367 --> 00:20:39,333
She captured him on video?

397
00:20:39,500 --> 00:20:41,600
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

398
00:20:41,700 --> 00:20:42,867
Wait.

399
00:20:43,733 --> 00:20:45,000
Did I hear you correctly?

400
00:20:47,133 --> 00:20:48,867
You mean Trixie was with her?

401
00:20:49,033 --> 00:20:51,467
They're always together, right?

402
00:20:51,567 --> 00:20:53,100
It's not their fault.

403
00:20:53,867 --> 00:20:56,200
They have nothing to do
with any of this.

404
00:20:56,367 --> 00:21:03,200
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

405
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:15,633
Gio, your water.

406
00:21:16,500 --> 00:21:17,400
[GIO] Thank you.

407
00:21:19,100 --> 00:21:20,133
Kiko...

408
00:21:20,233 --> 00:21:21,833
There's no right time
to bring this up.

409
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:23,367
[MARTIN EXHALES DEEPLY]

410
00:21:24,167 --> 00:21:26,300
Leon and I were supposed
to meet.

411
00:21:26,433 --> 00:21:28,633
But the police caught him.

412
00:21:31,700 --> 00:21:33,467
Martin, what is it?

413
00:21:36,533 --> 00:21:39,800
My siblings and I saw something
that we think...

414
00:21:39,900 --> 00:21:41,133
[MARTIN INHALES DEEPLY]

415
00:21:41,233 --> 00:21:42,633
...has something to do
with the treasure.

416
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:45,200
What? You found it?

417
00:21:45,367 --> 00:21:46,233
No.

418
00:21:48,033 --> 00:21:49,100
But we did find clues

419
00:21:49,233 --> 00:21:52,367
that we think will help us
find this treasure.

420
00:21:52,533 --> 00:21:53,567
Seriously?

421
00:21:54,267 --> 00:21:55,833
You believe that, too?

422
00:21:55,967 --> 00:22:00,767
Jade, if Andy is that desperate
to be part of the hotel...

423
00:22:00,900 --> 00:22:03,167
It means
the treasure might be real.

424
00:22:04,033 --> 00:22:05,600
[MARTIN] The bottom line is...

425
00:22:06,533 --> 00:22:10,267
If it's true what Juan said
about Andy knowing about this...

426
00:22:10,400 --> 00:22:13,067
I'm certain he's also looking
for the clues we found.

427
00:22:13,200 --> 00:22:18,167
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

428
00:22:18,333 --> 00:22:20,367
That's why he badly wants
to be part of Hotel 88.

429
00:22:20,467 --> 00:22:22,367
[KIKO] If that is
Andy's target...

430
00:22:23,400 --> 00:22:26,200
He might have something
to do with our fathers' deaths.

431
00:22:27,400 --> 00:22:29,433
Besides giving justice
to Leon...

432
00:22:29,567 --> 00:22:32,867
We can also give justice
to the death of our fathers.

433
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:39,867
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

434
00:22:42,767 --> 00:22:43,767
[PHONE RINGS]

435
00:22:45,233 --> 00:22:46,900
"Edward: You're not answering
my calls.

436
00:22:47,067 --> 00:22:47,967
I'm almost at your house."

437
00:22:48,100 --> 00:22:55,200
[CAR ENGINE REVVING]

438
00:22:57,333 --> 00:22:58,767
[OBJECTS RUSTLING]

439
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:01,067
[CAR DOOR SHUTS]

440
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:08,233
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

441
00:23:16,533 --> 00:23:17,733
[JUSTIN] Where's she going?

442
00:23:20,267 --> 00:23:21,300
[EDWARD] Jade.

443
00:23:23,500 --> 00:23:24,533
Edward.

444
00:23:26,633 --> 00:23:30,100
- Edward, please, go home.
- Jade. No.

445
00:23:30,233 --> 00:23:31,767
Didn't I tell you
I wouldn't abandon you?

446
00:23:31,900 --> 00:23:34,933
- Especially not now.
- Let's talk about it next time.

447
00:23:35,033 --> 00:23:36,700
For now, please,
go home, Edward.

448
00:23:36,833 --> 00:23:37,633
Go! Go home!

449
00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:40,133
What's the problem with me
visiting you?

450
00:23:40,300 --> 00:23:42,933
You hung up on me,
and now you're pushing me away?

451
00:23:43,067 --> 00:23:44,600
I'll just message you, okay?

452
00:23:44,700 --> 00:23:46,433
- I'll call you. I don't--
- Jade!

453
00:23:46,533 --> 00:23:48,467
- Justin?
- Why is he here?!

454
00:23:48,633 --> 00:23:50,700
- Justin!
- What are you doing here?!

455
00:23:50,833 --> 00:23:52,100
He's leaving, please!

456
00:23:52,233 --> 00:23:53,767
- Edward, please! Just go!
- Leave! Leave!

457
00:23:53,900 --> 00:23:55,167
Justin!

458
00:23:58,267 --> 00:24:00,200
- [JADE] Please.
- Just leave, man.

459
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:04,800
I'm not talking to you.

460
00:24:09,333 --> 00:24:11,667
Justin, Jade,
what's going on?

461
00:24:12,067 --> 00:24:14,300
Leave! I don't ever want
to see you around here!

462
00:24:14,400 --> 00:24:16,367
- Why?! Tell me!
- What do you mean, why?

463
00:24:16,500 --> 00:24:18,033
- Please go home!
- I don't understand!

464
00:24:18,167 --> 00:24:19,500
Don't touch me!

465
00:24:21,167 --> 00:24:22,467
Why are you even meddling?

466
00:24:22,667 --> 00:24:24,467
Because you can't see
that no one wants you here.

467
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:26,633
- Well, why do you care?
- Hey!

468
00:24:26,767 --> 00:24:27,733
Don't bother.

469
00:24:29,133 --> 00:24:31,500
[KIKO] Edward,
don't you understand?

470
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:33,400
Would you rather
this turn messy?

471
00:24:33,533 --> 00:24:34,667
I'm not here to cause trouble!

472
00:24:34,800 --> 00:24:36,400
Well, what are you
doing here, huh?!

473
00:24:36,533 --> 00:24:37,900
Why are you even here?!
Tell me!

474
00:24:38,033 --> 00:24:39,533
Justin! Please!

475
00:24:39,700 --> 00:24:42,033
He's going home. Edward,
you're going home, right?

476
00:24:42,200 --> 00:24:43,267
Go home.

477
00:24:44,200 --> 00:24:45,733
Is this about my dad?

478
00:24:45,867 --> 00:24:52,667
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

479
00:24:57,733 --> 00:24:59,767
<i>I want to talk to you
about the partnership.</i>

480
00:24:59,900 --> 00:25:01,767
<i>Didn't you get the call
from our lawyer?</i>

481
00:25:02,067 --> 00:25:03,233
<i>The partnership
did not push through.</i>

482
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:06,700
<i>Maybe you're forgetting that
you're the one who came to me.</i>

483
00:25:07,667 --> 00:25:08,867
<i> Sir, sir, sir, sir.</i>

484
00:25:08,967 --> 00:25:10,567
<i>I saw something
in Almazan's car.</i>

485
00:25:10,733 --> 00:25:13,033
<i>I have a video that shows
they're not whom he talked to.</i>

486
00:25:15,067 --> 00:25:16,900
<i>- What's that?
- Where'd that come from?</i>

487
00:25:17,633 --> 00:25:18,733
<i> Did you hear that?</i>

488
00:25:22,833 --> 00:25:23,733
<i> Juan...</i>
